 reservoir, 180 l</li>\r\n	<li>Test specimen bracket</li>\r\n	<li>Corrosion-resistant, stable support rods to hold the test specimen at bench height</li>\r\n	<li>Floor grid</li>\r\n	<li>Extended depth “U” profile groove on right-hand side for measuring and supply lines</li>\r\n	<li>Calibration in salt spray test (+35 °C test space temperature/+49 °C humidifier temperature)</li>\r\n	<li>Calibration in condensed water test (+40 °C test space temperature).</li>\r\n	<li>Ventilation device complying with DIN 50 014, clause 5 ambient temperature</li>\r\n	<li>Automatic water reservoir for DIN EN ISO 6270-2 [DIN 50 017 KFW] / EN ISO 6988 [DIN 50 018]</li>\r\n	<li>Test chamber floor drain with diaphragm valve for DIN EN ISO 6270-2\r\n[DIN 50 017 KFW] / EN ISO 6988 [DIN 50 018].</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Options</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ventilation device for DIN 50 014, clause 5 ambient temperature</li>\r\n	<li>Demineralization cartridge</li>\r\n	<li>Air compressor</li>\r\n	<li>Precipitation collector</li>\r\n	<li>Precipitation measurement and display</li>\r\n	<li>Measuring cable ports, each 50 mm or 100 mm Ø, free choice of location on left, front or rear wall of the test chamber</li>\r\n	<li>Triangular window (only SC/KWT 450)</li>\r\n	<li>SO<sub>2</sub> gas dosing device for EN ISO 6988 [DIN 50 018] manual operation, (automatic operation only possible in combination with SC/KWT equipment)</li>\r\n	<li>Hood locking, safety lock switch prevents opening of hood, e. g. in case of SO<sub>2</sub> atmosphere</li>\r\n	<li>Additional brine reservoir, 500 l</li>\r\n	<li>Interface RS 422/485 network card</li>\r\n	<li>Simpati* software package for Windows</li>\r\n	<li>Air conditioning unit</li>\r\n	<li>Brine mixing with circulation pump 200 l or 500 l</li>\r\n	<li>Other sizes, e. g. 2,000 l, or customized accessories are available upon request</li>\r\n</ul>'),(669,108,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(670,108,'additional_options',''),(671,108,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(690,112,'_edit_lock','1438200833:3'),(691,112,'_edit_last','3'),(692,112,'product_features','<ul>\r\n	<li>Gas dosing with thermal mass flow controller, concentration ranges from ppb to ppm</li>\r\n	<li>Inner test cabinet with connection for gas sampling and entry port NW 50mm</li>\r\n	<li>Air exchange rate in inner test cabinet can be set between one and four per hour</li>\r\n	<li>Door with window included in basic equipment</li>\r\n	<li>Specimen can be observed (inner test cabinet is made of acrylic glass (PMMA))</li>\r\n	<li>Up to four gasses can be dosed simultaneously</li>\r\n	<li>Inner test cabinet, shelf and door are made of acrylic glass</li>\r\n	<li>Pressure monitoring between inner test cabinet and outside as a safety feature</li>\r\n	<li>Compliance with test standards such as IEC 60068-2-60, IEC 60068-2-42/43, ISO 21207 and others</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTest gases\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>H<sub>2</sub>S</li>\r\n	<li>SO<sub>2</sub></li>\r\n	<li>Cl<sub>2</sub> with carrier gas N<sub>2</sub> (nitrogen)</li>\r\n	<li>NO<sub>2</sub>, with carrier gas synthetic air</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Standard Version Corrosive Gas Test System</h4>\r\nCabinet Extension (firmly mounted at the left side of the cabinet) including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1 gas dosing line with thermal mass flow controller and feeding line leading into the gas container</li>\r\n	<li>Gas distribution system</li>\r\n	<li>Purging gas line</li>\r\n	<li>Air change system</li>\r\n	<li>Pressure guide</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n1 auxiliary cabinet made of PMMA (120 l, 270 l, 380 l) including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Support grid of PMMA</li>\r\n	<li>Sample gas connection</li>\r\n	<li>Entry port at the right side, Ø 50 mm</li>\r\n	<li>Door made of PMMA</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nCommissioning, functional test and test run in our company'),(693,112,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(694,112,'additional_options','Other test gases available upon request'),(695,112,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(696,113,'_edit_lock','1438703527:3'),(697,113,'_edit_last','3'),(698,113,'product_features','<ul>\r\n	<li>Total access chamber lid stays open at 60˚ angle</li>\r\n	<li>Chamber lid gasketed with closed cell foam material</li>\r\n	<li>Lid equipped with quick-release latch hardware</li>\r\n	<li>Pressure relief vent with collector filter</li>\r\n	<li>Removable stainless steel wire grate specimen platform</li>\r\n	<li>Removable spray nozzles</li>\r\n	<li>Compressed air pressure regulation system with filter and trap</li>\r\n	<li>(2) adjustable interval digital timers and (1) counter timer</li>\r\n	<li>Compressed air dual tower air drier system dries air to a -85˚F dewpoint level</li>\r\n	<li>115-1-60 V power in with an amp draw of 5 amps</li>\r\n	<li>Interior light with exterior switch</li>\r\n</ul>'),(699,113,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(700,113,'additional_options','The new removable EZ Load Front Panel, an option available on Envirotronics’ Dust Chambers, allows the test product to be placed on the specimen rack without having to lift it over the chamber wall and lower it on the rack. It’s easy to load and easy on your back.\r\n\r\n<strong><u> </u></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Custom sizes available consult with your local salesperson</li>\r\n	<li>Many options available - contact your local salesperson for complete list</li>\r\n</ul>'),(701,113,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(702,114,'_edit_lock','1438703554:3'),(703,114,'_edit_last','3'),(704,114,'product_features','<ul>\r\n	<li>Total access chamber lid stays open at 60 degree angle</li>\r\n	<li>Chamber lid is gasketed with closed cell foam material</li>\r\n	<li>Lid is equipped with quick-release latch hardware</li>\r\n	<li>Pressure relief vent with filter</li>\r\n	<li>Removable stainless steel wire grate specimen platform</li>\r\n	<li>Removable spray nozzles</li>\r\n	<li>Compressed air pressure regulation system with filter and trap</li>\r\n	<li>(2) adjustable interval digital timers and (1) counter timer</li>\r\n	<li>Compressed air dual tower air drier system dries air to a -85˚F/-65˚C dewpoint level</li>\r\n	<li>115-1-60 V power in with an amp draw of 5 Amps</li>\r\n	<li>Interior light with exterior switch</li>\r\n</ul>'),(705,114,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(706,114,'additional_options','The new removable EZ Load Front Panel, an option available on Envirotronics’ Dust Chambers, allows the test product to be placed on the specimen rack without having to lift it over the chamber wall and lower it on the rack. It’s easy to load and easy on your back. • Custom sizes available consult with your local salesperson • Many options available - contact your local salesperson for complete list'),(707,114,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(708,115,'_edit_lock','1438375327:3'),(709,115,'_edit_last','3'),(710,115,'product_features','<ul>\r\n	<li>According to state-of-the-art manufacture the test cabinets are of a modular design and are ready to be installed.</li>\r\n	<li>The whole system is designed to be used under extreme conditions and guarantees reliable functioning and a long service life.</li>\r\n	<li>Independent of design and condition of the test specimen a constant dust density is reached due to special high-capacity compressed air nozzles, which leads to reliable test results.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Special Advantages at a Glance</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Easy operation</li>\r\n	<li>Modular design and ready to be installed</li>\r\n	<li>Switch cabinet in protection type IP 54</li>\r\n	<li>Easily-accessible system components guarantee shortest service and maintenance time</li>\r\n	<li>Low requirement of energy</li>\r\n	<li>Feet individually adjustable in height</li>\r\n	<li>Exterior finish</li>\r\n	<li>Amply dimensioned, user friendly loading door with special sealing</li>\r\n	<li>The unit mainly consists of the cubic test chamber with dust funnel fitted below the base.</li>\r\n	<li>The housing of the test chamber is made of sandwich panels. An acrylic glass door, equipped with a window wiper is fitted to the front of the test chamber. Optimum seal of the test chamber is ensured by special circumferential rubber seals. A shelf made of galvanized steel is located above the funnel on which the specimens are placed.</li>\r\n	<li>A replaceable exhaust air filter is mounted in the machine compartment of the test chamber.</li>\r\n	<li>Dust formation inside the test chamber is achieved by blowing in compressed air through special nozzles. The fine cement dust is blown into the upper test space by intensive air movement. The depositing fine dust particles are collected in the funnel and returned to the dust chamber. The dust is kept dry by a heating device fixed to the floor. The compressed air in the test chamber is passed to the outside through the replaceable exhaust air filter. A built-in pressure reducer with oil and water separator serves for fine adjustment of pressure in front of the nozzle. The solenoid valve installed in the compressed air supply pipe is actuated by the control system, i.e. it opens or closes according to the pre-set times of the test cycle.</li>\r\n	<li>The electrical section is installed in the switch cabinet fitted to the test chamber side wall. This switch cabinet will be connected to the power supply by means of a plug.</li>\r\n	<li>The switch cabinet is wired in accordance with the VDE regulations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Control System</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>S!MPAC* is a self-monitoring, digital 32 bit measuring and control system and has been designed especially for the use in test chambers. Thanks to its computing efficiency S!MPAC* meets the requirements of process technology and facilitates the input due to the touch panel that has been especially developed by Weiss Envirotronics.</li>\r\n	<li>The system is operated by means of the integrated color touch display. The display provides information on the current test time. Its function keys are available for direct switching on and off of testing. It has an alarm display and an acoustic alarm. The diagnosis system is activated on the touch screen display at the touch of a button.</li>\r\n	<li>Control is governed by the 32-bit I/0 system S!MPAC* with integrated soft PLC. A web server can place test and diagnosis and maintenance information on the intranet via Ethernet if desired.</li>\r\n	<li>However, since the USB interface is routed to the outside it still presents a certain danger potential, so that, theoretically, the computer system can be jeopardized by the installation and activation of malicious programs.</li>\r\n	<li>In order to avoid this risk potential we recommend the deactivation of the USB interface.</li>\r\n</ul>'),(711,115,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(712,115,'additional_options',''),(713,115,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(726,118,'_edit_lock','1438806061:3'),(727,118,'_edit_last','3'),(728,118,'product_features','<ul>\r\n	<li>The ozone measuring and control system continuously takes samples of gas volume and automatically corrects (closed control circuit) any losses/fluctuations of the O3 concentration.</li>\r\n	<li>Because of its instability (ca. 30 min), the ozone is generated onsite from clean air or oxygen close to where it is required.</li>\r\n</ul>'),(729,118,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(730,118,'additional_options',''),(731,118,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(756,123,'_edit_lock','1438201388:3'),(757,123,'_edit_last','3'),(758,123,'product_features','The Weiss systems are leaders in technology and state-of-the-art. Our equipment includes the following special features as standard:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Homogenous conditioning of the test space.</li>\r\n	<li>Measuring inputs for resistance thermometers in four-wire connection.</li>\r\n	<li>Possibility for automatic programming of complete temperature profiles.</li>\r\n	<li>Digital 32-bit measuring and control system (S!MCON/32*) allowing the connection of a PC and a printer.</li>\r\n	<li>The calibrations performed by WEISS are based on the valid standards and are traceable to national and international measurement standards.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFunction Reliability\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The entire system is designed for use under extreme conditions. High quality materials and sturdy design ensure reliability and durability. Some examples:</li>\r\n	<li>The test chamber is made from vapor-tight material (inside and outside) that resists impact and corrosion (see technical data).</li>\r\n	<li>The special construction of the wall elements combines high stability and superior insulation with minimum weight.</li>\r\n	<li>A double door seal combined with a lockable door ensures an absolute seal of the test chamber, even under extreme climatic conditions.</li>\r\n	<li>An adjustable over and under temperature protection (specimen protection according to EN 60519-2,1993 thermal safety class2) ensures protection of individual specimens.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBackground Emission\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Low background emissions are essential to obtain reliable test results. To meet the EPA/CARB/EN standards the limit value must not exceed 50 mg HC within 4 h.</li>\r\n	<li>For our Mini SHED (up to 6m³ volume) we guarantee a background emission of less than 7 mg HC within 4 h according to EPA §86.117-96a.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe above values can be further reduced by applying a special seal for the SHED gate (quoted as an option). Using this special seal the following background emission will be achieved: approx. 3,5 mg HC within 4 h according to EPA §86.117-96a (or our Mini SHED up to 6m³ volume).'),(759,123,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(760,123,'additional_options',''),(761,123,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(791,129,'_edit_last','2'),(792,129,'_wp_page_template','default'),(793,129,'_edit_lock','1444737663:8'),(794,130,'_edit_last','2'),(795,130,'_wp_page_template','page-service.php'),(796,130,'_edit_lock','1439238288:3'),(797,131,'_edit_last','2'),(798,131,'_wp_page_template','page-resources.php'),(799,131,'_edit_lock','1443729522:8'),(800,132,'_edit_last','2'),(801,132,'_wp_page_template','default'),(802,132,'_edit_lock','1443122543:8'),(815,135,'_menu_item_type','post_type'),(816,135,'_menu_item_menu_item_parent','0'),(817,135,'_menu_item_object_id','132'),(818,135,'_menu_item_object','page'),(819,135,'_menu_item_target',''),(820,135,'_menu_item_classes','a:1:{i:0;s:0:\"\";}'),(821,135,'_menu_item_xfn',''),(822,135,'_menu_item_url',''),(833,137,'_menu_item_type','post_type'),(834,137,'_menu_item_menu_item_parent','0'),(835,137,'_menu_item_object_id','130'),(836,137,'_menu_item_object','page'),(837,137,'_menu_item_target',''),(838,137,'_menu_item_classes','a:1:{i:0;s:0:\"\";}'),(839,137,'_menu_item_xfn',''),(840,137,'_menu_item_url',''),(853,140,'_menu_item_type','post_type'),(854,140,'_menu_item_menu_item_parent','0'),(855,140,'_menu_item_object_id','129'),(856,140,'_menu_item_object','page'),(857,140,'_menu_item_target',''),(858,140,'_menu_item_classes','a:1:{i:0;s:0:\"\";}'),(859,140,'_menu_item_xfn',''),(860,140,'_menu_item_url',''),(897,146,'_edit_lock','1438201585:3'),(898,146,'_edit_last','3'),(899,146,'product_features','The Spray and Splash Water Test Systems can perform tests according to the following standards. However, standardized special options are sometimes necessary to fulfill these.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>DIN EN 60 529-1:2000</li>\r\n	<li>DIN EN 60 034-5:2001</li>\r\n	<li>DIN 40 050-9:1993</li>\r\n	<li>DIN IEC 68, T2-18, method Rb 2.1</li>\r\n	<li>SAE Standard J575, 1993 (option)</li>\r\n	<li>JIS D 0203 – 1994, Tests R1/R2/S1/S2 (option)</li>\r\n	<li>MIL-STD-810F, Method 506.4 (option)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWith the Weiss standard Spray and Splash Water Test Systems tests according to IP X3 and IP X4 can be performed. Picture 1 shows a principle sketch of a test according to DIN EN 60 529.\r\n<h3>Application</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>IP X1/X2 (drip device, Option)</li>\r\n	<li>IP X3/X4 (swiveling tube, Standard)</li>\r\n	<li>IP X3/X4 (spray head, Option)</li>\r\n	<li>IP X5/X6  (jet nozzle, Option)</li>\r\n	<li>IP X9K (high pressure jet nozzle, Option)</li>\r\n</ul>'),(900,146,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(901,146,'additional_options',''),(902,146,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(903,147,'_edit_lock','1438628826:3'),(904,147,'_edit_last','3'),(905,147,'product_features','<ul>\r\n	<li>Solution Plus Touchscreen Controller</li>\r\n	<li>Full opening left-hand hinged door</li>\r\n	<li>Emergency stop push-button</li>\r\n	<li>(2) 4\" (102 mm) access ports</li>\r\n	<li>Interior light</li>\r\n</ul>'),(906,147,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(907,147,'additional_options','<ul>\r\n	<li>Many additional options available, contact your local salesperson for complete list</li>\r\n	<li>Custom sizes available consult with your local salesperson</li>\r\n</ul>'),(908,147,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(909,148,'_edit_lock','1439400353:2'),(910,148,'_edit_last','2'),(911,148,'product_features','<ul>\r\n	<li>Heavy-duty floors slope to perimeter drains</li>\r\n	<li>Solid one-piece construction</li>\r\n	<li>Prolong soak at high temperature and high humidity</li>\r\n	<li>Nominal 6-inch high-temperature non-setting fiberglass insulation</li>\r\n	<li>Vapor-proof interior lights with external switches</li>\r\n	<li>Floor loading up to 1,000 lbs psf. Extended up 10,000 psf.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;'),(912,148,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(913,148,'additional_options','<ul>\r\n	<li>Range of personnel and vehicle door sizes</li>\r\n	<li>Pneumatic door latches</li>\r\n	<li>Product shelves</li>\r\n	<li>Interior fixturing</li>\r\n	<li>Machine Module Standard Features</li>\r\n	<li>Completely self-contained including heating, cooling, air circulation, and instrumentation systems</li>\r\n	<li>Dual air circulation blowers with solid stainless steel jackshafts and external motors</li>\r\n	<li>Water-cooled refrigeration packages standard; air-cooled systems optional</li>\r\n	<li>Nichrome wire heating elements with fusible link</li>\r\n	<li>Solid state heat switching</li>\r\n	<li>Stainless steel plenum</li>\r\n	<li>Compatibility with four post simulators or dynamometers</li>\r\n	<li>HC/CO monitoring of vehicle under test</li>\r\n	<li>Complete customized operator interface software package</li>\r\n	<li>Complete installation packages</li>\r\n	<li>Custom sizes available consult with your local salesperson</li>\r\n	<li>Many options available - contact your local salesperson for complete list</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;'),(914,148,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(915,149,'_edit_lock','1438374879:3'),(916,149,'_edit_last','3'),(917,149,'product_features','<ul>\r\n	<li>Workspace volume 3.4m3</li>\r\n	<li>Workspace dimensions\r\nWxDxH 2000 x 1150 x 1510mm\r\nIrradiation unit</li>\r\n	<li>Type of irradiation 2 x 4 kW\r\nMetal halide global lamps</li>\r\n	<li>Irradiation intensity\r\n800 to 1200 W/m2 with reference to the test area, steplessly adjustable</li>\r\n	<li>Uniformity ±5% with reference to the test area</li>\r\n	<li>Test area 1700 x 800 mm, at a distance of at least 600 mm below the ceiling glazing</li>\r\n	<li>Spectral radiation distribution Global radiation 280 to 3000 nm, recommended for aging tests</li>\r\n	<li>Basis CIE Pub. No. 85 Tab 4</li>\r\n	<li>Parts DIN 75220 Tab. 1 Column 2/4</li>\r\n	<li>Radiation modulation &lt;1%</li>\r\n	<li>Output stability ±1%</li>\r\n</ul>'),(918,149,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(919,149,'additional_options',''),(920,149,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(921,150,'_edit_lock','1438659287:3'),(922,150,'_edit_last','3'),(923,150,'product_features','<ul>\r\n	<li>Several basic versions are available as temperature conditioning and climate versions with test space volumes of 2.6 and 3.4 m<sup>3 </sup>and a temperature range of between -70°C to +180°C</li>\r\n	<li>Dimensions and outputs can be adjusted to the customers requirements if needed</li>\r\n	<li>In the temperature range of +10 °C to +90 °C, a relative humidity of 10 to 98 % can be achieved</li>\r\n	<li>Specified standard temperature change rates (from 100 °C/h to 200 °C/h) can be realized</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Test chambers with an extra-high test space</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Basic test chamber versions are available for test space volumes between 1.5 and 3.1 m<sup>3</sup></li>\r\n	<li>Temperature range from -70 °C to +180 °C</li>\r\n	<li>Available as temperature or as climate test chambers</li>\r\n	<li>Especially providable for large PV modules</li>\r\n</ul>'),(924,150,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(925,150,'additional_options',''),(926,150,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(945,154,'_edit_lock','1438633680:3'),(946,154,'_edit_last','3'),(947,154,'product_features','<ul>\r\n	<li>Shorter heating, process, and cooling times compared to conventional methods, as a result energy is saved.</li>\r\n	<li>The products are heated in the microwave. The furnace chamber itself is not heated and does not have to be cooled down.</li>\r\n	<li>Use of metal parts, e. g. conventional metal tools and feeding systems, in the microwave field.</li>\r\n	<li>Specific, volumetric heating of products: Microwaves penetrate into the material directly and heat the product. As a result, heating rates and output can be increased considerably.</li>\r\n	<li>High product quality by sufficient homogeneity of the microwave fields: Thanks to the use of thermoelectric foils additional positive effects and material characteristics are achieved.</li>\r\n	<li>The systems designed extend from the laboratory up to the large scale that is needed in aircraft industry along with other fields of study.</li>\r\n</ul>'),(948,154,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(949,154,'additional_options',''),(950,154,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(951,155,'_edit_lock','1438633631:3'),(952,155,'_edit_last','3'),(953,155,'product_features','<ul>\r\n	<li>Process chamber (hexagon) equipped with 24 magnetrons for the generation of microwaves</li>\r\n	<li>Process chamber can be moved out of outer housing for maintenance purposes</li>\r\n	<li>Charging of process chamber via charging trolley with auxiliary trolley</li>\r\n	<li>Outer housing with cooling fan and switch cabinet integrated in service area</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Special Features</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Temperature recording in process chamber via optical fiber temperature sensor</li>\r\n	<li>Selection of individual magnetrons via industrial PC with special software</li>\r\n	<li>Homogeneous microwave field</li>\r\n</ul>'),(954,155,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(955,155,'additional_options',''),(956,155,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(957,156,'_edit_lock','1438633575:3'),(958,156,'_edit_last','3'),(959,156,'product_features','<ul>\r\n	<li>Outer housing covered with electro-galvanized steel plate RAL 9002</li>\r\n	<li>Working chamber made from stainless steel</li>\r\n	<li>Fan for cooling of magnetrons</li>\r\n	<li>Openings in both side walls</li>\r\n	<li>Access ports for resin pipes, thermocouples etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Connection pieces for process, supply and exhaust air</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Special Features</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Movable design</li>\r\n	<li>Hexagonal design of working chamber</li>\r\n	<li>Homogeneous microwave field</li>\r\n	<li>Volumetric heating of products (oven remains cold)</li>\r\n	<li>Measuring of temperature in working chamber temperature via fiber-optical temperature sensors</li>\r\n	<li>Control of individual magnetrons via S!MCON 32</li>\r\n</ul>'),(960,156,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(961,156,'additional_options',''),(962,156,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(969,158,'_edit_lock','1439327036:3'),(970,158,'_edit_last','3'),(971,158,'product_features','<ul>\r\n	<li>Outer casing stainless steel (material no. 1.4301)</li>\r\n	<li>IR surface lamp integrated in base and hood</li>\r\n	<li>Double-walled folding hood<