.\r\n\r\n<strong>Advantages</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Easy handling of the system</li>\r\n	<li>Simplified maintenance and cleaning</li>\r\n	<li>Safe working conditions for operating staff, due to the fact that no risks can evolve from hazardous additives to the system</li>\r\n	<li>Environmentally friendly</li>\r\n	<li>Low operating costs</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Product range</strong>\r\n\r\nWe offer dry heat sterilizers for the clean room specifications ISO 5 and 7 in accordance with DIN EN ISO 14644-1. All series can be produced as a free standing unit or prepared for wall installation, as a serving-hatch version with front and rear doors for separation of sterile and non-sterile working areas. The serving-hatch version is equipped with electric locks, thus ensuring that only one door at a time can be opened.'),(1079,179,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(1080,179,'additional_options',''),(1081,179,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(1082,180,'_edit_lock','1438631585:3'),(1083,180,'_edit_last','3'),(1084,180,'product_features','If you wish to sterilize quickly, cost-effectively, and reliably the dry heat sterilization method is an attractive alternative to other available systems on the market.\r\n\r\nThis method only employs air, thus enabling sterilization to be carried out at high temperatures. Dependent on the temperature level, the sterilization process is considerably faster than other methods and is time saving and economical with low investment costs. Thanks to the high temperatures, the sterilization process requires no chemicals, providing further advantages.\r\n\r\n<strong>Advantages</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Easy handling of the system</li>\r\n	<li>Simplified maintenance and cleaning</li>\r\n	<li>Safe working conditions for operating staff, due to the fact that no risks can evolve from hazardous additives to the system</li>\r\n	<li>Environmentally friendly</li>\r\n	<li>Low operating costs</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Product range</strong>\r\n\r\nWe offer dry heat sterilizers for the clean room specifications ISO 5 and 7 in accordance with DIN EN ISO 14644-1. All series can be produced as a free standing unit or prepared for wall installation, as a serving-hatch version with front and rear doors for separation of sterile and non-sterile working areas. The serving-hatch version is equipped with electric locks, thus ensuring that only one door at a time can be opened.'),(1085,180,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(1086,180,'additional_options',''),(1087,180,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(1088,181,'_edit_lock','1438631549:3'),(1089,181,'_edit_last','3'),(1090,181,'product_features','<ul>\r\n	<li>Outer housing of stainless steel, material class No. 1.4301</li>\r\n	<li>Inner housing of stainless steel, material class No. 1.4301</li>\r\n	<li>Push-through design with a door at front and rear</li>\r\n	<li>Electrical door locking mechanism</li>\r\n	<li>Switch box of stainless steel for separate wall attachment</li>\r\n	<li>Wall frame for flush mounting</li>\r\n	<li>5 shelves with wire mesh racks of stainless steel, material class No. 1.4541</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Special Features</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hygiene test as per DIN 58947 with test report</li>\r\n	<li>For use as per DIN 58946</li>\r\n</ul>'),(1091,181,'_product_features','field_55809dbfeeb63'),(1092,181,'additional_options',''),(1093,181,'_additional_options','field_55809f397125f'),(1094,182,'_edit_lock','1438631494:3'),(1095,182,'_edit_last','3'),(1096,182,'product_features','<ul>\r\n	<li>Outer housing made of stainless steel, material no. 1.4301</li>\r\n	<li>Inner housing made of stainless steel material no. 1.4301, seam-welded, GMP version</li>\r\n	<li>HEPA filter group in the side panel</li>\r\n	<li>Push-through design with electromechanical door locking mechanism in both doors</li>\r\n	<li>2-step fresh air fan with HEPA filter on the pressure side and F5 preliminary filter on the suction side</li>\r\n	<li>S!MCON/32 program c