or of large\r\ncomponents.','SC Walk-In','','publish','closed','closed','','sc-walk-in','','','2015-08-10 20:10:14','2015-08-10 20:10:14','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=105',177,'product','',0),(106,3,'2015-06-22 20:44:52','2015-06-22 20:44:52','The Climate-Alternating-Corrosion Test Chamber type SC 1000/15-60 IU meets the requirements of standard DIN 50 021/DIN EN ISO 9227 and allows the performance of corrosion alternating tests according to VDA Test 621-415 B with freezing (\"VDA New\").','SC 1000/15-60 IU','','publish','closed','closed','','sc-100015-60-iu-2','','','2015-07-20 21:06:41','2015-07-20 21:06:41','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=106',176,'product','',0),(107,3,'2015-06-22 20:45:35','2015-06-22 20:45:35','The SC/KWT 1000 is a performance salt fog and condensed water test chamber. The chamber has a climate extension that allows for cycles with controlled humidity and drying/ventilation as well as combination alternating tests with cycles.','SC/UKWT','','publish','closed','closed','','scukwt','','','2015-07-29 18:28:14','2015-07-29 18:28:14','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=107',175,'product','',0),(108,3,'2015-06-22 20:45:55','2015-06-22 20:45:55','The SC/KWT series is a climate-alternating chamber allowing for reproducible, accelerated corrosion testing in compliance with the requirements of DIN, ISO, ASTM, DEF, MIL-STD, etc. The wide-angle top loading test chamber hood helps with loading heavy, or bulky test specimens. Two sizes are available.','SC/KWT','','publish','closed','closed','','sckwt','','','2015-07-29 20:15:54','2015-07-29 20:15:54','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=108',174,'product','',0),(112,3,'2015-06-22 20:51:05','2015-06-22 20:51:05','<h3>Noxious Gas Test</h3>\r\nTo prove the resistance of the technical products to corrosive gases, Weiss developed the corrosion test chambers cabinets series BSB. The BSB enables an exact dosage of the corrosive gases with a climate conditioned air volume. The main constituents of the corrosive, atmospheric trace elements are: sulphur dioxide (SO2), nitrogen oxide (NOx), hydrogen sulphide (H2S) and chlorine gas (CL2).\r\n\r\nThe basic unit consists of a test system of series Klima 3000 with 340, 600 and 1000 liters.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','BSB Test Cabinet','','publish','closed','closed','','bsb-test-cabinet','','','2015-07-10 22:03:00','2015-07-10 22:03:00','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=112',173,'product','',0),(113,3,'2015-06-22 20:54:32','2015-06-22 20:54:32','Envirotronics takes the back pain out of loading test specimens in dust chambers. The new removable EZ Load Front Panel, an option available on Envirotronics\' Dust Chambers, allows the test product to be placed on the specimen rack without having to lift it over the chamber wall and lower it on the rack. It\'s easy to load and easy on your back.\r\n\r\nThe removable panel is held firmly in place by compression latches. The latch pressure and the front panel gasket create a positive seal that keeps the dust out of your lab and inside your chamber, where it belongs.\r\n\r\nThe front Panel has been removed, allowing easy access to the specimen rack\r\n\r\n*The EZ Load Panel is an option that may not be available on all models.\r\n\r\nThe Envirotronics D Series Dust Chamber is designed to test a component\'s resistance to a dust-filled environment as defined in SAE Dust Test Specifications J-575, Section 4.5. The product is placed on the specimen rack and dust is agitated throughout the chamber by injecting compressed air into each of the dust troughs. The dust then settles, covering the product under test.\r\n\r\nA compressed air pressure regulation system with filter and trap is provided for connection to your air supply. Air must be supplied at a minimum pressure of 80 psi and 10 CFM. The D Series\' control timers allow pre-setting the agitation, the number of agitation intervals, and the number of cycles with automatic shutdown at the end of the preset number of cycles.','D60','','publish','closed','closed','','d24','','','2015-08-03 20:56:19','2015-08-03 20:56:19','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=113',172,'product','',0),(114,3,'2015-06-22 20:54:52','2015-06-22 20:54:52','The D Series chamber is constructed of 16 gauge sheet metal with an air-dried lacquer-sprayed finish. The hinged lid gives full access to the workspace and is available with the option of viewing windows. In the larger D60 model, (2) 8\" to 10\" fan blades are mounted in the chamber to keep the dust in an agitated state. The pressure relief vent which is provided will prevent pressure buildup within the cabinet while preventing the escape of dust material.','D24','','publish','closed','closed','','d60','','','2015-08-04 15:54:55','2015-08-04 15:54:55','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=114',171,'product','',0),(115,3,'2015-06-22 20:55:22','2015-06-22 20:55:22','Dust tests are mainly performed to test functioning of electronic components under extreme environmental conditions. Various standards specify e.g. the test duration and the composition of dust used. The dust is filled in the funnel below the test space. The formation of dust within the test space is effected by compressed air injection through four special nozzles. The dust is blown and swirled in upper test space by intensive air movement.\r\n\r\nDust tests are mainly performed to test functioning of electronic components under extreme environmental conditions. Various standards specify e.g. the test duration and the composition of dust used. The standard SAE J 575 is performed with three to five kilograms unburnt Portland cement (according to ASTM C 150-77). Portland cement is especially characterized by its fine grain size. This dust is filled in the funnel below the test space. The formation of dust within the test space is effected by compressed air injection through four special nozzles. The dust is blown and swirled in upper test space by intensive air movement.\r\n\r\nThe pulse time for this action is 2 to 15 seconds with a brake of 15 minutes between the single impulses.','ST','','publish','closed','closed','','st','','','2015-07-31 20:44:19','2015-07-31 20:44:19','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=115',169,'product','',0),(118,3,'2015-06-22 21:14:02','2015-06-22 21:14:02','For testing organic materials, in particular testing elastomers the ozone endurance test if of utmost importance.','WT/WK-OZ','','publish','closed','closed','','wtwk-oz','','','2015-08-05 20:22:33','2015-08-05 20:22:33','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=118',168,'product','',0),(123,3,'2015-06-22 21:16:42','2015-06-22 21:16:42','The Weiss Envirotronics VT Mini Shed Chambers are used for fuel tank permeation tests or for HC emission tests in fuel carrying vehicle components. The equipment consists of a volume compensation device, explosion-proof test-space, an analyzer, lighting, a window, a refueling port and purging and safety equipment.','VT/VV MINI-SHED','','publish','closed','closed','','vtvv-mini-shed','','','2015-07-29 20:25:18','2015-07-29 20:25:18','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=123',170,'product','',0),(129,4,'2015-06-22 21:35:56','2015-06-22 21:35:56','<h3><strong>Sales &amp; Service Locations</strong></h3>\r\nEnvirotronics maintains sales offices around the globe to assist you with every detail of your environmental test equipment requirements. Our sales offices are staffed with experienced professionals who will ensure that your experience with Envirotronics is a rewarding one whether you require a simple \"standard\" temperature chamber or a complex custom system.\r\n\r\nWe have service centers located strategically around the U.S. which are staffed with experienced technicians ready to assist you with replacement parts , emergency service, installation and equipment relocation, preventive maintenance programs, instrumentation upgrades and calibration, and refrigerant modifications.','Locations','','publish','open','open','','locations','','','2015-07-30 18:14:16','2015-07-30 18:14:16','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?page_id=129',25,'page','',0),(130,4,'2015-06-22 21:36:24','2015-06-22 21:36:24','<h2>Supporting Our Equipment</h2>\r\nAfter-the-sale support is an integral component of our business. Our Product Support Group offers complete engineering and technical support, prompt emergency service, instrumentation upgrades and equipment relocation services located across the United States and globally. Other aspects of the Product Support program include service contracts as well as upgrades to environmentally safe refrigerants. Service is available for all Weiss Envirotronics equipment as well as most other chamber makes and models.','Services','','publish','open','closed','','services','','','2015-07-29 17:24:26','2015-07-29 17:24:26','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?page_id=130',31,'page','',0),(131,4,'2015-06-22 21:36:37','2015-06-22 21:36:37','','Resources','','publish','open','open','','resources','','','2015-07-15 17:16:57','2015-07-15 17:16:57','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?page_id=131',30,'page','',0),(132,4,'2015-06-22 21:36:52','2015-06-22 21:36:52','Weiss Envirotronics takes great pride in providing equipment that has been designed and manufactured by some of the most experienced people in the industry. Our strong and continuous growth pattern has been a result of a progressive management philosophy, providing quality equipment and an unequaled dedication to after sales support. We take great pride in being a leader in the industry. Developing new designs, utilizing the latest technology and implementing state-of-the-art manufacturing techniques will ensure our position in the industry.\r\n\r\nOriginally established in 1979 for the purpose of servicing environmental test chambers, Weiss Envirotronics has become an industry leader in the design, manufacture, and modification of environmental test chambers for temperature, humidity, vibration, altitude, thermal shock, portable shock chambers, burn-in chambers, custom equipment, fluid chillers, air burn-in systems, SAE dust chambers, combustion air units, automotive test systems, drive-in chambers, conditioned rooms, and forced air ovens. Weiss Envirotronics’ quality management system is registered to ISO9001-2008 ANSI/ISO/ASQ Q9001-2008 (Exclusions: None).\r\n\r\nWeiss Envirotronics is a member of the Weiss  Group, a division of the Schunk Group of Heuchelheim, Germany. Weiss  has over 50 years of experience in the manufacture of environmental test chambers and employs 1,700 people in 21 group companies across Europe and in China. Weiss is a member of the Schunk-Group. For further information about Weiss, please visit our website.\r\n\r\nThe Schunk-Group is a group of globally-active technology companies with a broad product and service spectrum in material technology and system engineering encompassing the areas of carbon technology and ceramics, environmental engineering and air conditioning, sinter metal technology, ultrasonics and enamel engineering. Ludwig Schunk and Karl Ebe established the company in 1913. The Schunk Group has over 60 companies and locations in 27 countries. The Group employs over 8,250 people around the world. For information about the Schunk-Group, please visit: <strong><strong>›</strong></strong><a href=\"http://www.schunk-group.com/\">www.schunkgroup.com</a>.\r\n\r\nAll Weiss Envirotronics equipment is manufactured in compliance with the appropriate military standards, ASTM specifications, or customer requirements. Weiss Envirotronics’ power panels are in compliance with UL508A First Edition dated April 25, 2001, NFPA79 requirements, and ETL labeled. Equipment shipping into Canada is certified to CAN/CSA C22.2 NO.14 and ETL labeled. Equipment shipping into the European markets, where applicable, has C.E. Declaration of Conformity certificates provided and is in compliance with European standards. When incorporated in equipment purchase specifications, our equipment is manufactured to conform to SEMI S2-0200, and SEMI S8-1000 guidelines.\r\n\r\nWeiss Envirotronics maintains a network of factory service centers in the US and Asia, and retains service contractors worldwide. Through these centers,  Weiss Envirotronics provides emergency service and repair, preventive maintenance contracts, spare and replacement parts, relocation services, and rebuilding or refurbishment of all makes of environmental test chambers. Weiss Envirotronics is an ISO/IEC 17025-2005 Edition (A2LA) accredited calibration facility.\r\n\r\nWe are committed to excellence in every aspect of our business, from our engineering capabilities and our customer service to our manufacturing processes and personnel.\r\n\r\nOur Corporate Headquarters is located at 3881 N. Greenbrooke SE, Grand Rapids, Michigan 49512, USA, This location has both office and manufacturing space. Additional service and manufacturing space is located one mile away.  Weiss Envirotronics is also located within minutes from the Gerald R. Ford International Airport.','About Us','','publish','open','open','','about-us','','','2015-08-28 20:21:57','2015-08-28 20:21:57','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?page_id=132',20,'page','',0),(135,4,'2015-06-22 21:38:16','2015-06-22 21:38:16',' ','','','publish','open','open','','135','','','2015-08-11 21:08:37','2015-08-11 21:08:37','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?p=135',42,'nav_menu_item','',0),(137,4,'2015-06-22 21:38:16','2015-06-22 21:38:16','','Service','','publish','open','open','','137','','','2015-08-11 21:08:37','2015-08-11 21:08:37','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?p=137',40,'nav_menu_item','',0),(140,4,'2015-06-22 21:39:59','2015-06-22 21:39:59',' ','',''