/png',0),(532,4,'2015-06-26 23:11:23','2015-06-26 23:11:23','','mini-slider2','','inherit','open','open','','mini-slider2','','','2015-06-26 23:11:23','2015-06-26 23:11:23','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/mini-slider2.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(539,3,'2015-06-29 15:36:09','2015-06-29 15:36:09','The Weiss ZKB 20/18 and the ZKB 20/18-B series are mobile air conditioning systems that have been specifically designed for mobile cleanrooms, command posts, and medical/rescue tents. These systems will operate reliably even at temperatures reaching up to +60° C with a cooling capacity up to 18 kW. The ZKB 20/18 comes standard with a patented fuel-powered heating capacity of up to 30 kW. Even with an outside temperature of -32°C tents can be comfortable for those inside. The heat-carrying medium is used to transfer heat into the tent where it is then supplied into the ventilation system. This indirect heating system prevents emissions from entering the tent space.','ZKB 20/18 ZKB 20/18-B','','publish','closed','closed','','zkb-2018-zkb-2018-b','','','2015-08-03 19:33:48','2015-08-03 19:33:48','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=539',15,'product','',0),(558,3,'2015-06-30 15:57:49','2015-06-30 15:57:49','<span style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: small;\">Remote Conditioners or Equipment Cooling Air units are used to deliver temperature conditioned air to remote enclosures. Our Remote Conditioners may also be designed to act as a stand-alone test chamber for even greater flexibility</span>','Remote Conditioners','','publish','closed','closed','','remote-conditioners','','','2015-11-02 18:57:52','2015-11-02 18:57:52','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=558',14,'product','',0),(562,2,'2015-06-30 16:03:26','2015-06-30 16:03:26','','Product Images','','publish','closed','closed','','acf_product-images','','','2015-06-30 16:03:26','2015-06-30 16:03:26','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=acf&#038;p=562',0,'acf','',0),(571,3,'2015-06-30 18:17:21','2015-06-30 18:17:21','<b>Explosion resistant heating oven and drying oven VFT 60/90</b>\r\n\r\nThe VFT 60/90 is an explosion resistant fresh air heating and drying oven. The oven is electrically heated and designed according to the fresh-air-principle. Due to the small floor space required it is also suitable for installation in laboratories and production departments. The advantages, e.g. no restriction on the volume of combustible solvents, suitable for solvents with the temperature classes T1, T2, T3, T4 in the explosion groups IIA and IIB, precise temperature uniformity in the whole working chamber.\r\n\r\nThe VFT 60/90 drying oven provides its safety concept of primary and secondary explosion protection measures for safe heat treatment processes in areas of the chemical, pharmaceutical, paint and basic material industry.','VFT 60/90','','publish','closed','closed','','vft-6090','','','2015-07-27 17:04:52','2015-07-27 17:04:52','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=571',13,'product','',0),(583,4,'2015-06-30 23:50:54','2015-06-30 23:50:54','','test','','inherit','open','open','','test','','','2015-06-30 23:50:54','2015-06-30 23:50:54','',31,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/test.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(590,4,'2015-07-01 17:23:24','2015-07-01 17:23:24','','Areas of Focus PDF','','publish','closed','closed','','acf_areas-of-focus-pdf','','','2015-07-21 20:51:44','2015-07-21 20:51:44','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=acf&#038;p=590',0,'acf','',0),(593,4,'2015-07-01 17:38:47','2015-07-01 17:38:47','','aof-automotive','','inherit','open','open','','aof-automotive','','','2015-07-01 17:38:47','2015-07-01 17:38:47','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/aof-automotive.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(594,3,'2015-07-01 17:41:32','2015-07-01 17:41:32','Fitotron® High Specification Plant Growth Chambers (HGC’s) are based on a modular design. Should your research requirements change, the chamber can be adapted to a new situation by exchanging or retrofitting your individual modules.\r\n\r\nIn addition to three chamber sizes, it is possible to modify light sources and intensity, airflow direction, temperature range and the internal maximum growing height. This flexible design allows the chambers to be modified for different applications and as such, provides a ‘future-proof’ investment.\r\n<h3>Lighting</h3>\r\nThe Fitotron® HGC range uses a combination of different lamps to simulate a daylight spectrum. Through the use of high frequency fluorescent lamps, dimming of light intensity from 100% to 10% is standard. \'Dawn/dusk\' is simulated by the addition of a high proportion of red light.\r\n\r\nAs an option, the height of the lamps can be adjusted using an external motor. This ensures that the growing conditions remain constant and the plants are not disturbed.\r\n\r\nMetal halide lamp modules with higher light intensities of 700 and 1000 µmols @ 500mm are available. The lamps are installed in a separate air-cooled lamp compartment, together with the UV light source.','Fitotron High Specification Growth Chambers','','publish','closed','closed','','fitotron-high-specification-growth-chambers','','','2015-08-03 18:54:17','2015-08-03 18:54:17','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=594',9,'product','',0),(595,3,'2015-07-01 17:43:42','2015-07-01 17:43:42','Fitotron® Standard Growth Room (SGR) offer unsurpassed accuracy and reliability in the control of temperature, humidity and lighting. State-of-the-art program technology and energy efficient lighting systems are used which provide unequalled reliability and durability. This sustainable design offers the end-user a cost-effective solution and durability. This sustainable design offers the end-user a cost-effective solution.\r\n<h3>Description</h3>\r\nFitotron® Walk-in’ Standard Growth Rooms enable the researcher to maintain controlled growing conditions of temperature and humidity in a 24hr period with independent selection of photoperiods. A full range of ‘day/night’ cycles with ‘dawn/dusk’ effects can be programmed.\r\nFitotron® Standard Growth Rooms allow the researcher access to most world climatic conditions whilst eliminating the variability found in nature.','Fitotron Standard Growth Rooms','','publish','closed','closed','','fitotron-standard-growth-rooms','','','2015-08-03 18:55:47','2015-08-03 18:55:47','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=595',12,'product','',0),(596,3,'2015-07-01 17:44:48','2015-07-01 17:44:48','Fitotron® Multi-tier Cultivation Rooms (MCR’s) have been specifically designed to suit a variety of different plant growth applications. They are ideal for research involving Arabidopsis and similar-sized plants.\r\n\r\nMCR’s can be assembled and fully operational within a short space of time - the ideal solution for immediate requirements. In addition, MCR’s can be fitted with a number of different shelf and lighting options to suit a wide range of biological applications.\r\n<h3>Lighting</h3>\r\nLighting can be specified by the user and is available in racks of 3 or 4 tiers. Lighting racks can be purchased independently of the room itself and are delivered as complete, free-standing ‘plug and play’ units, incorporating the growing surface, lighting and air distribution. Each lighting bank ensures even distribution of airflow across the shelves, resulting in minimum temperature variations.\r\nLighting in the MCR range provides medium intensity of 250 μmol m<sup>-2</sup>s<sup>-1</sup> @ 300mm for the 3 tier version and 180 μmol m<sup>-2</sup>s<sup>-1</sup> @ 300mm for the 4 tier version. Lighting racks are supplied with fluorescent lamps, each level of which is individually dimmable from an intensity of 100% to 10%. LED lighting can also be fitted if required.\r\nUsers also have the option of adding light boxes, within which specimens can be cultured at different temperature and lighting conditions to the plants grown on the open light racks. Users can therefore have different conditions within the same room.\r\n<h3>Performance</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Temperature range (lights on and lights off): +15°C to +30°C</li>\r\n	<li>Lighting intensity 3 tiers: 250 μmol m<sup>-2</sup>s<sup>-1</sup> @ 25°C 300mm below lights</li>\r\n	<li>Lighting intensity 4 tiers: 180 μmol m<sup>-2</sup>s<sup>-1</sup> @ 25°C 300mm below lights</li>\r\n	<li>Humidity range* (lights on): 50%RH to 75%RH</li>\r\n	<li>Humidity range* (lights off): 50%RH to 80%RH</li>\r\n	<li>Dewpoint range* (lights on): +10°C to +22°C</li>\r\n	<li>Dewpoint range* (lights off): +10°C to +24°C</li>\r\n</ul>','Fitotron Multi-Tier Cultivation Rooms','','publish','closed','closed','','fitotron-multi-tier-cultivation-rooms','','','2015-08-03 18:54:46','2015-08-03 18:54:46','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=596',10,'product','',0),(597,3,'2015-07-01 17:46:15','2015-07-01 17:46:15','The Weiss Envirotronics Fitotron® Standard Growth Room (SGR) offers unrivaled accuracy and reliability in the control of temperature, humidity and lighting. State-of-the-art programmer technology and energy efficient lighting systems are used to provide unequalled dependability and durability. This sustainable design offers the end-user a cost-effective solution and durability. This sustainable design offers the end-user a cost-effective solution.\r\n<h3>Description</h3>\r\nFitotron® Walk-in’ Standard Growth Rooms permits the researcher to maintain controlled growing conditions of temperature and humidity in a 24hr period with independent selection of photoperiods. A full range of ‘day/night’ cycles with ‘dawn/dusk’ effects can be programmed.\r\nFitotron® Standard Growth Rooms allow the researcher access to most world climatic conditions whilst eliminating the variability found in nature.\r\n<h3>Features</h3>\r\nSGR’s are available with growth areas from 1.4m<sup>2</sup> to 24.5m<sup>2</sup> and with lighting up to 500 µmol m<sup>-2</sup>s<sup>-1</sup> plus full humidity control. Alternatively, we can design and build to suit individual requirements.\r\n<h3>Service</h3>\r\nWeiss Envirotronics is a world leader in the design, build, installation and servicing of controlled environments, environmental test chambers and test rooms. Building on over 40 years experience, our Fitotron® Plant Growth equipment incorporates the latest developments in technology, many having been originated by the company’s own design team.\r\n\r\nOur proven innovation and design incorporates the very latest advances in state-of-the-art programmer technology and energy efficient lighting systems, culminating in Standard Growth Rooms with a wider performance range, greater control of conditions and with unequalled reliability and durability.\r\n\r\nOur combination of high quality components, design, and manufacturing expertise enables us to offer outstanding control performance and reassurance of the integrity of the results of temperature, humidity, light and atmospheric testing. Our policy of continual liaison with leading researchers ensures we maintain our premier position as suppliers of high quality plant growth and associated facilities.\r\nWeiss Envirotronics provide a range of Fitotron® Standard Growth Rooms. Alternatively, we can design custom-fit solutions for your requirements.','Fitotron High Specification Growth Rooms','','publish','closed','closed','','fitotron-high-specification-growth-rooms','','','2015-08-03 18:55:20','2015-08-03 18:55:20','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=597',11,'product','',0),(603,4,'2015-07-01 18:09:10','2015-07-01 18:09:10','','aof-pharma','','inherit','open','open','','aof-pharma','','','2015-07-01 18:09:10','2015-07-01 18:09:10','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/aof-pharma.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(605,3,'2015-07-01 18:32:52','2015-07-01 18:32:52','The Envirotronics EC Series Moist Cabinet/Curing Chambers are specifically designed for use in the making and curing of hydraulic cement and concrete test specimens.\r\n\r\nThe EC Series is equipped with both dry and submerged storage. Its large workspace has an operating temperature range of 15.6° C to 37.8° C and humidity range of 40% to 98% R.H. as limited by a +4.5° C dewpoint temperature. Temperature control is maintained through a Partlow 7000 controller/recorder and humidity is controlled with a solid state R.H. transmitter/sensor.\r\n\r\nAccess to each stainless steel construction workspace area is through large fully opening hinged doors. Each access area holds stainless steel wire shelves and 6\" deep cement curing trays.<em>\r\n</em>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>»</strong><strong>Conforms to ASTM C 511-06</strong></p>\r\nTop and bottom curing trays have a Fill/Drain fixture located at the back/bottom of the tray (as shown in the detail photo above). The Fill/Drain helps to simplify the draining, precipitate removal, cleaning, and refilling process. The top tanks also have a sampling valve in front. The center trays have a drain only. Each tray also has an overflow outlet which allows overflow to drain to a lower tray. The overflow drains back to the main chamber reservoir, keeping the solution in circulation. The water reservoir in the chamber base also has an inlet/outlet drain for easy cleaning.\r\n\r\nThe EC Series uses a one HP single-stage refrigeration system utilizing \"environmentally friendly\" refrigerant HP62 (R404A) and a local air-cooled condenser.\r\n\r\nEC Series Moist Cabinet/Cement Curing Chambers are available in 20, 40, 70, and 100 cubic foot models*. Other size chambers available upon request.\r\n\r\n*workspace area is approximate\r\n\r\nThe EC Series conforms with ASTM C 511-06<em>\r\n</em>','EC Series','','publish','closed','closed','','ec-series','','','2015-08-03 21:51:31','2015-08-03 21:51:31','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=605',8,'product','',0),(610,4,'2015-07-01 19:47:32','2015-07-01 19:47:32','','aof-heat-technology','','inherit','open','open','','aof-heat-technology','','','2015-07-01 19:47:32','2015-07-01 19:47:32','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/aof-heat-technology.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(612,4,'2015-07-01 19:48:14','2015-07-01 19:48:14','','aof-electronics','','inherit','open','open','','aof-electronics','','','2015-07-01 19:48:14','2015-07-01 19:48:14','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/aof-electronics.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(615,3,'2015-07-02 19:27:27','2015-07-02 19:27:27','','OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA','OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA','inherit','open','open','','olympus-digital-camera','','','2015-07-02 19:27:27','2015-07-02 19:27:27','',148,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/WW-series-chamber_weiss_blue-May-2015.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(616,3,'2015-07-02 20:17:25','2015-07-02 20:17:25','','Main','','inherit','open','open','','main','','','2015-07-02 20:17:25','2015-07-02 20:17:25','',112,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/Main.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(617,3,'2015-07-02 20:18:12','2015-07-02 20:18:12','','Main','','inherit','open','open','','main-2','','','2015-07-02 20:18:12','2015-07-02 20:18:12','',112,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/Main1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(618,3,'2015-07-02 20:42:25','2015-07-02 20:42:25','','MAINWUT-TS60_offen','','inherit','open','open','','mainwut-ts60_offen','','','2015-07-02 20:42:25','2015-07-02 20:42:25','',47,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/MAINWUT-TS60_offen.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(619,3,'2015-07-02 20:53:23','2015-07-02 20:53:23','','WUT-TS60_offen','','inherit','open','open','','wut-ts60_offen','','','2015-07-02 20:53:23','2015-07-02 20:53:23','',29,'