\n\r\nLocation: Main Office-Grand Rapids, Mi\r\n\r\nReporting Line: Department Lead/Asst. Production Manager/Production Manager/COO\r\n\r\n<strong>Overview of position: </strong>\r\n\r\nThis position interconnects wired electrical panels to the environmental test chamber through following electrical schematics/blueprints/mechanical engineering drawings. The position also wires the components to the power panel.\r\n\r\n<strong>Essential functions of the position levels: </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Entry Level I </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cuts different gauge wires in pre-determined lengths</li>\r\n	<li>Cuts interconnect in pre-determined lengths</li>\r\n	<li>Checks in parts received from stockroom against pick list to verify part numbers and quantities</li>\r\n	<li>Drills out J-Boxes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Level II </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Level I functions</li>\r\n	<li>Reads and understands blue prints/specs/electrical schematics</li>\r\n	<li>Reads and understands parts list</li>\r\n	<li>Reads and understands cut list</li>\r\n	<li>Wires switches</li>\r\n	<li>Lays out J-Boxes and wire panels</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Level III </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Level I and II functions</li>\r\n	<li>Lays out location of J-Boxes</li>\r\n	<li>Lays out and wires a job per engineering drawings</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Level IV </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Level I, II, and III functions</li>\r\n	<li>Performs 110V Job continuity test</li>\r\n	<li>Performs point to point verification</li>\r\n	<li>Quality checks a job</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Department Lead </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Coordinates level I, II, III, and IV employees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Qualifications/Requirements: </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>History of good attendance</li>\r\n	<li>Possession of High School Diploma or GED</li>\r\n	<li>Task oriented</li>\r\n	<li>Preferred: previous experience working in a manufacturing environment</li>\r\n	<li>Preferred: experience and education in electrical</li>\r\n	<li>Experience reading blueprints, specs, and electrical schematics</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to read cut and parts lists</li>\r\n	<li>Good math skills</li>\r\n	<li>Demonstrated ability to follow procedures</li>\r\n	<li>Accuracy in reading a tape measure, wire gauge and cutting wires</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to read, understand parts list and fill out quality check sheets</li>\r\n	<li>Experience using power tools including drill, grinder, cutoff wheel</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to obtain the necessary tools for this position: tape measure, screwdriver, channel locks, wire strippers, hammer, nut drivers, crimpers</li>\r\n	<li>Job entails: sitting, standing, walking, bending, stooping, squatting, kneeling, crawling, climbing, balancing, lifting, and carrying (occasionally up to 30 lbs) See statement of activity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFor more information on this Position, please contact our Human Resources Department at: <strong><a href=\"mailto:personnel@envirotronics.com\">personnel@envirotronics.com</a></strong>\r\n\r\nTo apply for a position please fill out the attached <a href=\"http://envirotronics.com/wp-content/uploads/Employment_Application_Form_WENV_v52.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">employment application</a>, save and email to <a href=\"mailto:personnel@envirotronics.com\">personnel@envirotronics.com</a>','Electrical Assembler','','trash','closed','closed','','electrical-assembler','','','2015-11-09 20:11:19','2015-11-09 20:11:19','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=career&#038;p=1364',5,'career','',0),(1365,3,'2015-07-16 21:55:47','2015-07-16 21:55:47','','Sussman Boiler ES Manual','','publish','closed','closed','','sussman-boiler-es-manual','','','2015-07-16 21:55:47','2015-07-16 21:55:47','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=manual&#038;p=1365',0,'manual','',0),(1366,3,'2015-07-16 21:55:31','2015-07-16 21:55:31','','ES_Manual','','inherit','open','open','','es_manual','','','2015-07-16 21:55:31','2015-07-16 21:55:31','',1365,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/ES_Manual.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1367,3,'2015-07-16 21:56:52','2015-07-16 21:56:52','','Barnstead B-pure Pressure Cartridge System Operation Manual','','publish','closed','closed','','barnstead-b-pure-pressure-cartridge-system-operation-manual','','','2015-07-16 21:56:52','2015-07-16 21:56:52','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=manual&#038;p=1367',0,'manual','',0),(1368,3,'2015-07-16 21:56:26','2015-07-16 21:56:26','','LT583X1BpureCartrdg','','inherit','open','open','','lt583x1bpurecartrdg','','','2015-07-16 21:56:26','2015-07-16 21:56:26','',1367,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/LT583X1BpureCartrdg.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1369,2,'2015-07-16 21:56:47','2015-07-16 21:56:47','<strong><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1802 size-full\" src=\"http://envirotronics.com/wp-content/uploads/people_manufacturing.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"234\" height=\"156\" />Job Description</strong>: <strong>Refrigeration Assembler</strong>\r\n\r\nLocation: Main Office-Grand Rapids, Mi\r\n\r\nReporting Line: Department Lead/Asst. Production Manager/Production Manager/COO\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Overview of position: </strong>\r\n\r\nThis position assembles the refrigeration system of the chamber through following blueprints/mechanical engineering drawings. This position starts with a structural steel frame and mounts components and does the line piping.\r\n\r\n<strong>Essential functions of the position levels: </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Entry Level I </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cuts copper</li>\r\n	<li>Applies Armaflex to refrigeration lines</li>\r\n	<li>Applies RTV732 (Spaz)</li>\r\n	<li>Sweeps and cleans department</li>\r\n	<li>Straps refrigeration lines, bulb sensors, and insulates lines</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Level II </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Level I functions</li>\r\n	<li>Mounts tanks, drip pans, compressors, oil separators, and valves</li>\r\n	<li>Installs switches</li>\r\n	<li>Insulates machine pack</li>\r\n	<li>Installs gauges</li>\r\n	<li>Pipes drains for water</li>\r\n	<li>Reads parts lists</li>\r\n	<li>Using math functions accurately—multiplication, division, conversion of decimals to fractions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Level III </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Level I and II functions</li>\r\n	<li>Reads, understands and interprets parts lists and mechanical engineering drawings</li>\r\n	<li>Sub-assembles refrigeration components</li>\r\n	<li>Performs soldering and brazing</li>\r\n	<li>Performs leak checks</li>\r\n	<li>Installs valve panels</li>\r\n	<li>Installs de-humid and evaporator coils</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Level IV </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Level I, II, III functions</li>\r\n	<li>Builds final assembly</li>\r\n	<li>Connects major sub-assemblies</li>\r\n	<li>Pressure checks at 200 PSI</li>\r\n	<li>Does water piping</li>\r\n	<li>Checks water piping at 60 PSI</li>\r\n	<li>Installs humidity systems-water socks, atomizing, demineralizing and recirculating water systems</li>\r\n	<li>Strategically mounts pipes and components, independently without guidance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Lead </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Coordinates work of Level I, II, III, IV employees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Qualifications/Requirements: </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Possession of High School Diploma or GED</li>\r\n	<li>History of good attendance</li>\r\n	<li>Task oriented</li>\r\n	<li>Preferred: previous experience working in a manufacturing environment</li>\r\n	<li>Preferred: experience and education in refrigeration, including wrapping, piping, soldering, brazing, and mounting of refrigeration components</li>\r\n	<li>Good math skills with ability to convert decimals to fractions</li>\r\n	<li>Demonstrated ability to follow procedures</li>\r\n	<li>Accuracy in reading a tape measure</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to read, understand parts list and fill out quality check sheets</li>\r\n	<li>Experience using power tools including drill and saws</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to obtain the necessary tools for this position: tape measure, screwdriver, wrenches, channel locks, copper cutters</li>\r\n	<li>Job entails: sitting, standing, walking, bending, stooping, squatting, kneeling, crawling, climbing, balancing, lifting, and carrying (occasionally up to 30 lbs) See statement of activity.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFor more information on this Position, please contact our Human Resources Department at: <a href=\"mailto:personnel@envirotronics.com\">personnel@envirotronics.com</a>\r\n\r\nTo apply for a position please fill out the attached <a href=\"http://envirotronics.com/wp-content/uploads/Employment_Application_Form_WENV_v52.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">employment application</a>, save and email to <a href=\"mailto:personnel@envirotronics.com\">personnel@envirotronics.com</a>','Refrigeration Assembler','','trash','closed','closed','','refrigeration-assembler','','','2015-11-09 20:11:24','2015-11-09 20:11:24','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=career&#038;p=1369',4,'career','',0),(1370,3,'2015-07-16 22:00:00','2015-07-16 22:00:00','','StarView Manual','','publish','closed','closed','','starview-manual','','','2015-07-16 22:00:00','2015-07-16 22:00:00','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/?post_type=manual&#038;p=1370',0,'manual','',0),(1371,3,'2015-07-16 21:59:51','2015-07-16 21:59:51','','StarVIEW','','inherit','open','open','','starview','','','2015-07-16 21:59:51','2015-07-16 21:59:51','',1370,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/StarVIEW.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1374,3,'2015-07-16 22:01:52','2015-07-16 22:01:52','','HammerInspCleaning(1)','','inherit','open','open','','hammerinspcleaning1','','','2015-07-16 22:01:52','2015-07-16 22:01:52','',0,'http://envirotronics.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/HammerInspCleaning1.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1375,3,'2015-07-16 22:03:44','2015-07-16 22:03:44','','Vibration Research Corp. Vibration View Manual','','publish','closed','closed','','vibration-research-corp-vibration-view-manual'